author: CNN
description: Arizona’s attorney general has sued the US House of Representatives over Republican Speaker Mike Johnson’s refusal to seat an Arizona member of Congress – who was elected in late September – due to the government shutdown. “This case is about whether someone duly elected to the House,” Kris Mayes and other attorneys wrote in the filing Tuesday, “may be denied her rightful office simply because the Speaker has decided to keep the House out of ‘regular session.’” #CNN #News
title: Speaker Johnson sued over refusal to swear in democrat needed for Epstein vote

author: CNN
description: Capital Area Food Bank distributed canned and dry goods to over 370 households of federal employees and contractors on Tuesday – they had been expecting around 150 people. The event was hosted by No Limits Outreach Ministries in Landover, Maryland and employees were required to present a government work ID to receive food. #CNN #news #federalworkers #governmentshutdown2025
title: Federal workers line up for food donations three weeks into shutdown

author: CNN
description: An Immigration and Customs Enforcement agent’s weapon discharged when the agent tried to grab an individual who apparently rammed into a vehicle that was part of a team of ICE and US marshals engaged in immigration enforcement, a law enforcement source tells CNN. The incident left two people, including a US marshal, injured.
title: Suspect and US Marshal injured in LA ICE incident

author: CNN
description: Olivia Ferney is a luxury accommodations agent who has gone viral for posting about phone calls with her high-end clients. Ferney says some of the calls are reenacted while the others are real.
title: Travel agent goes viral after posting about rich clients’ complaints

author: CNN
description: The audacious jewelry heist at the Louvre’s Apollo Gallery has inspired users on social media to re-create their own playful versions of the brazen theft.
title: People mock the Louvre’s security after heist

author: CNN
description: Republican New York City mayoral candidate Curtis Sliwa is facing renewed pressure to drop his bid for mayor. Some Republicans have rallied behind Andrew Cuomo, who is running as an independent, in a bid to stop Democratic nominee Zohran Mamdani from becoming mayor. Cuomo and his allies are pushing Sliwa to drop out after successfully getting Mayor Eric Adams to leave the race, arguing the former New York governor could then consolidate opposition to Mamdani, a democratic socialist. #CNN #News
title: Republican NYC mayoral candidate Curtis Sliwa on defying pressure to exit the race

author: CNN
description: Capital Area Food Bank distributed canned and dry goods to over 370 households of federal employees and contractors on Tuesday – they had been expecting around 150 people. The event was hosted by No Limits Outreach Ministries in Landover, Maryland and employees were required to present a government work ID to receive food. #cnn #cnnnews
title: Federal workers line up for food donations three weeks into shutdown

author: CNN
description:
Tropical Storm Melissa formed Tuesday morning in the Caribbean, fueled by record-hot ocean water. Here’s what we know about where it could go next.
#cnn #news
title: Tropical Storm Melissa forms in the Caribbean

author: CNN
description: The New York Times has reported that President Trump wants the Department of Justice to financially compensate him for various previous federal investigations. CNN's Kasie Hunt leads a panel to discuss. #CNN #News
title: NYT: Trump demands $230 million from DOJ for past investigations

author: CNN
description: Vice President JD Vance downplayed concerns about the fragility of the Israel-Hamas ceasefire while speaking in Israel, even as some Trump administration officials are privately concerned the deal could fall apart, sources familiar with the matter told CNN.
title: Vance downplays concerns over Israel-Hamas ceasefire

author: CNN
description: There are no plans for President Donald Trump to meet with Russian President Vladimir Putin “in the immediate future,” according to a Trump administration official, seeming to reverse course after Trump said last week that the two leaders were expected to meet “within two weeks or so, pretty quick.” CNN’s Kristen Holmes reports and CNN national security analyst Beth Sanner breaks down the impact on Russia’s war with Ukraine.  #CNN #News
title: ‘No plans’ for Trump meeting with Putin in near future, according to admin official

author: CNN
description:
A TikTok video appears to show a Homeland Security agent pointing a pepper ball gun from a moving truck in Illinois. A federal judge says the incident is “troubling” and has called for answers. CNN has reached out to DHS and local police for more information about the incident.

#cnn #news #immigration #dhs #illinois
title: Judge questions use of 'force' by DHS agent

author: CNN
description:
Congress remains in a standoff over health care subsidies 21 days into the government shutdown. Republican Senate Majority Leader John Thune told CNN's Manu Raju there’s no “plan B” for ending the impasse, signaling Republicans will keep pressuring Democrats to simply accept the House’s funding bill.

#CNN #News #Politics #Shutdown
title: Republican leader says no 'plan B' 21 days into the shutdown

author: CNN
description: Virginia Giuffre feared she might “die a sex slave” at the hands of Jeffrey Epstein and his circle, the prominent accuser wrote in a posthumous memoir. Six months after her death by suicide in Australia, Giuffre’s memoir “Nobody’s Girl” contains harrowing details of the abuse she allegedly suffered as a teenager, and her years attempting to get justice for herself and her fellow victims.  #CNN #News
title: Virginia Giuffre’s book reveals fresh claims about Jeffrey Epstein and Prince Andrew

author: CNN
description: CNN's Max Foster breaks down key excerpts and revelations in 'Nobody's Girl,' the memoir by prominent Jeffrey Epstein accuser, Virginia Giuffre, published posthumously. #cnn #news
title: Virginia Giuffre's posthumous memoir published

author: CNN
description: Japan has elected staunch conservative politician Sanae Takaichi, as its next prime minister, the country's first woman to hold this position. CNN's Hanako Montgomery looks at what this appointment could mean for Japanese women. #cnn #news
title: Will a female PM improve the lives of Japanese women?

author: CNN
description: 23-year-old Democratic activist Harry Sisson responds to an AI video posted by President Donald Trump depicting Trump dropping what appeared to be sewage on Sisson and other protesters attending the "No Kings" rally. #CNN #News
title: Activist targeted in Trump's AI sewage video responds

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump’s hopes for a quick meeting with Russian President Vladimir Putin may be stalled after sources familiar with the matter told CNN that an expected pre-meeting between the world leaders’ key foreign affairs aides this week had been tabled, at least for now.  #CNN #News
title: Trump’s hope for quick second summit with Putin may be stalled

author: CNN
description:
Two judges, who were appointed by President Donald Trump, overturned a temporary restraining order blocking the mobilization of federal troops in Portland. CNN's Nick Watt reports from outside an ICE facility in Oregon about the ruling and what legal hurdles remain for the Trump admin.

#CNN #News #Trump #Portland #NationalGuard
title: What's next in Portland after court rules Trump can deploy troops?

author: CNN
description: Samuel Kangethe has lived in Michigan for 16 years, first as a student, then as a husband and father. In August, he made the difficult decision to leave his family behind and return home to Kenya, driven by anxiety over the possibility of sudden deportation. #news #cnn
title: 'Daddy wasn't running away': One immigrant's decision to self-deport

author: CNN
description: House Speaker Mike Johnson (R-LA) has defended an AI video posted by President Trump. The video shows Trump flying a plane over 'No Kings' protesters and dropping what appears to be feces on crowds below. #cnn #trump #nokings
title: Johnson calls Trump AI video 'satire'

author: CNN
description: Authorities arrested a man inside Hartsfield-Jackson Atlanta International Airport on Monday after his family alerted police that he was armed and headed to the airport to “shoot it up.” The man, Billy Joe Cagle, was not armed when he was arrested but police found an “AR-15 assault rifle” in his vehicle parked outside, authorities said.  #CNN #News
title: Man arrested at Atlanta airport after making threats

author: CNN
description: Paul Ingrassia’s nomination to lead the Office of Special Counsel is dead on arrival in the Senate, per Senate Majority Leader John Thune, who declared Monday night that “he’s not going to pass” after Politico reported on racist text messages allegedly sent by Ingrassia to a group chat.  #CNN #News
title: Politico report on racists texts appears to derail Trump nominee

author: CNN
description: Demolition of the White House East Wing began Monday as President Donald Trump adds a $200 million, 90,000-square-foot ballroom.  #CNN #News
title: Demolition begins to replace White House East Wing with Trump’s ballroom

author: CNN
description: Former French President Nicolas Sarkozy left his residence to go to La Santé Prison in Paris on Tuesday to serve a five-year sentence. He was sentenced for criminal conspiracy last month for his role in a scheme to finance his 2007 presidential campaign with funds from Libya in exchange for diplomatic favors. Sarkozy has stressed that he is innocent and has appealed his conviction. #CNN #news
title: France's Former President Nicolas Sarkozy leaves home for prison

author: CNN
description:
What if we could understand what the animals around us are saying? Aza Raskin is the co-founder of @earthspeciesproject, a nonprofit that's using AI to decode animal communication. He explains how AI identifies language patterns across the animal kingdom, which species we’re closest to understanding, and how to mitigate harms that could result from this new technology.

Listen to the full episode of CNN’s Terms of Service podcast: http://swap.fm/l/tosyt102125

#cnn #news #tech #technology #animals #pets #nature #language
title: Can AI really help us understand our pets? | Terms of Service

author: CNN
description: Video from the crime scene outside the Louvre in Paris appears to show the tools used by thieves who broke into the museum on Sunday, stealing an "inestimable" value of jewels. #cnn #louvre #paris
title: What footage of crime scene reveals about Louvre heist

author: CNN
description: Here’s a look inside the Paris prison once home to dictators and spies — now housing former French president Nicolas Sarkozy. #CNN #News
title: The French prison now home to a former president

author: CNN
description: Staunch conservative Sanae Takaichi was elected Japan’s first female prime minister by the country’s parliament. #cnn #news #japan #takaichi
title: Japan's Sanae Takaichi becomes first female Prime Minister

author: CNN
description: Former President Joe Biden has completed a course of radiation therapy as he battles prostate cancer, a spokesperson for Biden told CNN. #cnn #news #biden #cancer
title: Biden completes a course of cancer treatment

author: CNN
description: An Alaska man was rescued from his flooded home after he became trapped and filmed the house drifting off of its foundation.
title: Home drifts off foundation in Alaska flood

author: CNN
description: CNN's Kaitlan Collins hosts Lawfare Senior Editor Anna Bower, who published a series of text messages she exchanged with Trump-appointed US Attorney in Virginia Lindsey Halligan about the Letitia James case. #CNN #News
title: Reporter publishes 'unsolicited' texts from Trump's handpicked prosecutor about Letitia James case

author: CNN
description: In a meeting at the White House, Donald Trump told Australia's ambassador to the US, Kevin Rudd, "I don't like you, and I probably never will." Rudd had previously posted negative comments about Trump on social media, which he deleted after taking the job. Trump's remarks to Rudd's face came during the President's first meeting with Prime Minister Anthony Albanese. After the incident, Rudd reportedly offered an apology to Trump, who accepted it.  #CNN #News #Australia
title: Trump tells Australian ambassador ‘I don’t like you’

author: CNN
description: CNN's Kaitlan Collins reports on the demolition of the White House East Wing as President Donald Trump adds a $200 million, 90,000-square-foot ballroom.
title: Trump kicks off East Wing demolition for ballroom

author: CNN
description: Precious artifacts snatched from Paris’s Louvre Museum Sunday include an emerald necklace set among more than 1,000 diamonds gifted by Napoleon to his second wife and other treasures of “inestimable” value. The thieves targeted the Louvre’s Apollo Gallery on the upper floor, which houses the French Crown Jewels. In the course of a brisk seven-minute heist, they broke into two high-security display cases and stole nine items, according to France’s culture ministry. The thieves left on motorcycles, police said. #CNN #News
title: 'Priceless' Louvre crown jewels stolen, international manhunt underway

author: CNN
description: Trump administration officials defended themselves in court as US District Judge Sara Ellis demanded explanations for their response to tense protests against immigration enforcement actions in Chicago. Ellis earlier this month issued a sweeping order restricting agents’ crowd control tactics, use of force and actions against journalists documenting protests in Chicago. During last week’s hearing, she said she had concerns about her order being followed. CNN's Whitney Wild shares insights from the latest hearing.
title: Judge questions Trump officials on response to protests

author: CNN
description: A man police identified as Billy Joe Cagle was arrested at Hartsfield-Jackson Atlanta International Airport after his family reported he was headed there to “shoot it up.”
title: Man arrested inside Atlanta airport after making threats
